  "prompt": "What is luvox good for?",
  "response": "Luvox (fluvoxamine) is an antidepressant medication primarily used to treat:\n\n1. Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder (OCD)\n- Most common and FDA-approved use\n- Helps reduce obsessive thoughts and compulsive behaviors\n\n2. Depression\n- Can be prescribed to treat major depressive disorder\n\n3. Anxiety disorders\n- Social anxiety disorder\n- Panic disorder\n- Generalized anxiety disorder\n\n4. Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)\n\nLuvox belongs to a class of medications called Selective Serotonin Reuptake Inhibitors (SSRIs), which work by balancing serotonin levels in the brain to improve mood and reduce symptoms of various mental health conditions.\n\nImportant notes:\n- Should only be taken under medical supervision\n- Prescription medication\n- Dosage varies depending on the condition being treated\n- May have side effects\n- Not suitable for everyone\n\nAlways consult a healthcare professional for personalized medical advice about using Luvox.",
